# Same concept applies to:

| API                  | Actually handled by                  |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| `fetch()`            | Native C++ networking layer          |
| `addEventListener()` | OS/browser event system              |
| `console.log()`      | Native stdout/console implementation |
| `Math.random()`      | Native random generator              |

---

# Important Insight

V8 only executes JavaScript.

Most Web APIs and Node.js APIs are implemented by:

* Browsers
* Node.js runtime
* OS-level system libraries

Mostly written in C/C++.

That’s why JavaScript can remain:

✔ Single-threaded
✔ Non-blocking
✔ Asynchronous

Because the heavy work happens outside the JS engine.

The event loop simply coordinates completed tasks back into JavaScript execution.

